This paper deals with image localization using deep learning techniques, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the impact of the loss function on the performance of neural networks, which is a key aspect of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves the use of a pose regression network, which is a common technique in robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper deals with RGB-only images, which is a subfield of multimedia (cs.MM).
